,000 miles of pipeline inspections have been completed since the incident. The spill caused significant environmental damage to Mill Creek and its floodplain.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-canadian-pipeline-company-will-pay-26-9-million-after-a-rupture-spilled-13000-barrels-of-oil-into-a-kansas-creek/articleshow/132414537.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-canadian-pipeline-company-will-pay-26-9-million-after-a-rupture-spilled-13000-barrels-of-oil-into-a-kansas-creek/articleshow/132414537.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-15T17:00:26+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132414825,imgsize-1592251.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists discover heat-resistant coral reefs across 71 countries that could help protect oceans]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132466800.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A groundbreaking study has revealed the extensive mapping of over 64,000 square miles of heat-resistant coral reefs globally, empowered by artificial intelligence across 71 nations and 100 territories. These extraordinary underwater locales feature traits that help coral ecosystems endure and rebound from intense marine heatwaves. The outcomes of this research present an essential blueprint for focused conservation financing and the safeguarding of marine life during the alarming bleaching epidemic.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-discover-64000-square-miles-of-heat-resistant-coral-reefs-across-71-countries-that-could-help-protect-the-worlds-oceans-for-decades/articleshow/132466800.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-discover-64000-square-miles-of-heat-resistant-coral-reefs-across-71-countries-that-could-help-protect-the-worlds-oceans-for-decades/articleshow/132466800.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-18T00:28:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132468793,imgsize-381998.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Peter Thiel: 'The next Bill Gates will not build an operating system' and a crucial business lesson]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132468745.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-peter-thiel-the-next-bill-gates-will-not-build-an-operating-system-and-a-crucial-business-lesson/articleshow/132468745.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/quote-of-the-day-by-peter-thiel-the-next-bill-gates-will-not-build-an-operating-system-and-a-crucial-business-lesson/articleshow/132468745.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-18T00:26:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132468768,imgsize-76486.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['People will pay because they have to': Trump Media pitches $100,000 monthly fee for faster Truth Social posts]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132467139.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/people-will-pay-because-they-have-to-trump-media-pitches-100000-monthly-fee-for-faster-truth-social-posts/articleshow/132467139.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/people-will-