ia.indiatimes.com/photo/132464875.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/h-1b-update-no-second-lottery-uscis-says-it-has-received-enough-petitions-for-fy-2027/articleshow/132464875.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/h-1b-update-no-second-lottery-uscis-says-it-has-received-enough-petitions-for-fy-2027/articleshow/132464875.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-17T21:16:03+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132464906,imgsize-71070.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists played human voices near Alaska salmon streams and found that bears and eagles fled]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132463469.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[New findings from Canadian researchers reveal that human sounds near Alaska's salmon streams significantly disturb wildlife, leading to grizzly bears avoiding feeding areas. This interference disrupts the natural nutrient transfer to surrounding forests, emphasizing the detrimental effects of human activity on essential ecosystem dynamics. Scientists propose enhanced land management practices to safeguard these critical ecological processes.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-played-human-voices-near-alaska-salmon-streams-and-found-that-bears-and-eagles-fled-disrupting-how-salmon-nutrients-move-into-forests/articleshow/132463469.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-played-human-voices-near-alaska-salmon-streams-and-found-that-bears-and-eagles-fled-disrupting-how-salmon-nutrients-move-into-forests/articleshow/132463469.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-17T21:00:27+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132464666,imgsize-351658.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Chinese CEO Yang Zhilin achieves huge AI milestone, Indian-origin entrepreneur says US was stupid enough to let him go]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132464340.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/chinese-ceo-yang-zhilin-achieves-huge-ai-milestone-indian-origin-entrepreneur-says-us-was-stupid-enough-to-let-him-go/articleshow/132464340.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/chinese-ceo-yang-zhilin-achieves-huge-ai-milestone-indian-origin-entrepreneur-says-us-was-stupid-enough-to-let-him-go/articleshow/132464340.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-17T20:44:02+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132464395,imgsize-65064.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Rare Atlantic Niña and Super El Niño may suppress hurricanes, lowering US landfall risk]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132462959.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A rare Atlantic Niña is developing alongside a strong Super El Niño event.  These ocean patterns may suppress hurricane formation in the Atlantic Ocean.  Increased wind shear and sinking air create an atmospheric shield against storms.  However, experts caution that a quieter season does not eliminate hurricane risks.  Residents in vulnerable areas should continue their normal hurricane preparations.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/a-rare-atlantic-nia-and-a-powerful-super-el-nio-may-work-together-to-suppress-atlantic-hurricanes-lowering-us-landfall-risk-but-not-removing-it/articleshow/132462959.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/a-rare-atlantic-nia-and-a-powerful-super-el-nio-may-work-together-to-suppress-atlantic-hurricanes-lowering-us-landfall-risk-but-not-removing-it/articleshow/132462959.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-17T19:34:13+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132462961,imgsize-97627.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists discover first-ever antidote to red tide toxin]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132463549.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a groundbreaking study, researchers have identified a frog protein capable of neutralizing saxitoxin, a harmful neurotoxin. This unique protein functions as a molecular sponge, effectively binding to the toxin in the bloodstream. Experiments on mice demonstrated its ability to prevent and even reverse the effects of lethal poisoning, offering significant possibilities for combatting paralytic shellfish poisoning incidents globally.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-discover-first-ever-antidote-to-red-tide-toxin-behind-shellfish-poisoning/articleshow/132463549.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-discover-first-ever-antidote-to-red-tide-toxin-behind-shellfish-poisoning/articleshow/132463549.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-17T19:59:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132463789,imgsize-216654.cms"/></item></channel></rss>